  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Using a sharp knife, score the <strong>duck skin</strong> on a diagonal, being careful not to cut through to the meat</p>\n<p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then add the <strong>scored duck</strong>, skin-side down, to a cold, dry pan over a low-medium heat</p>\n<p>Cook for 10-15 min, skin-side down only, or until the skin is golden and crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>red chilli<span class=\"text-danger\">[es]</span></strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop ﬁnely</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2211.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once golden, transfer the <strong>duck</strong>, skin-side up, to a baking tray</p>\n<p>Put the tray into the oven for 10-12 min for medium</p>\n<p>Tip: Cook for 3-5 minutes further if you prefer your duck well done</p>\n<p>Once cooked, set the duck aside, cover, and leave to rest for at least 10 min</p>\n<p> </p>",
